Name: Flinders
Description:
The Division of Flinders consists of:

  • part of the Mornington Peninsula Shire Council, and
  • The unincorporated areas of Elizabeth, French, and Sandstone Islands.
ProductsAndIndustry: Healthcare, retail, dairy farms, fishing, poultry, orchards, light industries, education and training, wineries, and tourism.
NameDerivation: Named in honour of Matthew Flinders, 1774-1814. Flinders was a well-known navigator and explorer who charted parts of the Australian coast. The adoption of the name Australia is due to him.
